Practice Question
Ex. 2: Design a simple HTML structure to display two customer testimonials side by side. Each testimonial should include the customer's name, photo, and a short comment about their experience. Utilize appropriate HTML elements to create the structure and content for the testimonial section.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Customer Testimonials</title>
<style>
  .testimonials {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin: 20px;
  }
  .testimonial {
    width: 48%;
    border: 1px solid #ccc;
    padding: 20px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .testimonial img {
    max-width: 100px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
